      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "# **Aim**\nAim is the most important mechanic, especially this season due to the little rotation and very good weapons for aiming. Although being very easy to aim this season, it is very hard to train. Keeping dedication and knowing what to train becomes very hard when you could be free building or looking flashy. \n## **How to improve aim:**\n- Method 1\n  - The best aim trainer in the world is Kovaaks (You can get it on Steam)\n  - No matter your skill level its 100% worth it to invest about $6-$10 on kovaaks\n  - Make sure to do this before you start playing Fortnite\n- Method 2\n  - Controller players I do not care how good your aim is , Aim duelling with make it 10x better \n  - You must aim duel daily to see improvements or as often as you can\n## **Choosing Your Sesitivity**\n- This is very important due to the need to control your mouse or joystick. Maybe your sensitivity is perfect. If your aim isn't naturally great, it is hard to find a perfect sensitivity.\n__High sensitivity:__\n- High sensitivity in any platform is very hard to control yet gives fast flicks and quick shots. \n- It is very hard to find improvement with a fast sensitivity without training with a lot of dedication.\n__ Low sensitivity:__\n- Low sensitivity allowed for control and even though flicking becomes harder, your tracking and smoothness goes up the roof. \n- Flicking can be trained although control is harder to train quickly. You can get away with little aim training but it essential to keep it in your routine.\n## **More tips for aim**\n- Mouse Control\n  - Controller players don't need mouse control but for KBM players, this is very important. \n  - It requires you to be comfortable with your mouse along with your setup. \n  - This allows you to be snappy with your mouse, almost making you look like you lock onto a target.",
